  "publicClaimBoundaries": {
    "safeClaims": [
      "GCA has a live public data contract for wallet verification, credit ledger, and GCA Member ledger records.",
      "The GCA Member data contract requires 1,000,000 GCA held for 30 consecutive days before a one-time 10,000 GCA member benefit review.",
      "The member ledger schema includes memberBenefitReviewEvidence fields for support and ledger review.",
      "The public member access page can submit account intake, read the current GCA balance through the backend, write eligible credit records, and queue qualifying member evidence.",
      "GCA Member activation requires a separate ADMIN_READ_TOKEN-protected operator review recorded in the append-only member review table.",
      "The legacy public members page can still generate a local pre-registration packet and run a browser-only read-only GCA balance preview with MetaMask eth_call.",
      "The controlled HTTPS integration verifies GCA balance with an ERC-20 balanceOf read before writing eligible ledger records."
    ],
    "doNotClaim": [
      "manual support can override wallet-balance verification",
